DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:20.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  ENV LANG=C.UTF-8 LC_ALL=C.UTF-8
  # Set working directory
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  # Install system dependencies
  RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      wget \
      git \
      build-essential \
      ca-certificates \
      curl \
      unzip \
      python3-dev \
      python3-pip \
      python3-setuptools \
      libffi-dev \
      libssl-dev \
      pkg-config \
      cython3 \
      && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # Install Miniconda for Python 3.6
  ENV CONDA_DIR=/opt/conda
  RUN wget --quiet https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-py36_4.9.2-Linux-x86_64.sh -O /tmp/miniconda.sh && \
      bash /tmp/miniconda.sh -b -p $CONDA_DIR && \
      rm /tmp/miniconda.sh && \
      $CONDA_DIR/bin/conda clean -tipsy
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/bin:$PATH
  # Create conda environment with python 3.6
  RUN conda create -n reltr python=3.6 -y
  SHELL ["conda", "run", "-n", "reltr", "/bin/bash", "-c"]
  # Activate conda environment and install packages
  RUN conda install pytorch==1.6.0 torchvision==0.7.0 cpuonly -c pytorch -y && \
      conda install matplotlib scipy numpy cython -y
  # Install pycocotools from github
  RUN pip install -U 'git+https://github.com/cocodataset/cocoapi.git#subdirectory=PythonAPI'
  # Clone the RelTR repository
  RUN git clone https://github.com/yrcong/RelTR.git /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  # Build native code for IoU computation and cython extension
  RUN cd lib/fpn && \
      sh make.sh && \
      python setup.py build_ext --inplace && \
      cd ../../
  # Set working directory and default shell
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  ENV CONDA_DEFAULT_ENV=reltr
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/envs/reltr/bin:$PATH
  CMD ["conda", "run", "-n", "reltr", "/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 1 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:20.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  ENV LANG=C.UTF-8 LC_ALL=C.UTF-8
  # Set working directory
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  # Install system dependencies
  RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      wget \
      git \
      build-essential \
      ca-certificates \
      curl \
      unzip \
      python3-dev \
      python3-pip \
      python3-setuptools \
      libffi-dev \
      libssl-dev \
      pkg-config \
      cython3 \
      && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # Install Miniconda for Python 3.6 using wget with retry logic
  ENV CONDA_DIR=/opt/conda
  RUN wget --tries=5 --timeout=30 https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-py36_4.9.2-Linux-x86_64.sh -O /tmp/miniconda.sh && \
      bash /tmp/miniconda.sh -b -p $CONDA_DIR && \
      rm /tmp/miniconda.sh && \
      $CONDA_DIR/bin/conda clean -tipsy
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/bin:$PATH
  # Create conda environment with python 3.6
  RUN conda create -n reltr python=3.6 -y
  SHELL ["conda", "run", "-n", "reltr", "/bin/bash", "-c"]
  # Activate conda environment and install packages
  RUN conda install pytorch==1.6.0 torchvision==0.7.0 cpuonly -c pytorch -y && \
      conda install matplotlib scipy numpy cython -y
  # Install pycocotools from github
  RUN pip install -U 'git+https://github.com/cocodataset/cocoapi.git#subdirectory=PythonAPI'
  # Clone the RelTR repository
  RUN git clone https://github.com/yrcong/RelTR.git /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  # Build native code for IoU computation and cython extension
  RUN cd lib/fpn && \
      sh make.sh && \
      python setup.py build_ext --inplace && \
      cd ../../
  # Set working directory and default shell
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  ENV CONDA_DEFAULT_ENV=reltr
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/envs/reltr/bin:$PATH
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 3 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:20.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  ENV LANG=C.UTF-8 LC_ALL=C.UTF-8
  # Set working directory to the root of the repository
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  # Install system dependencies
  RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      wget \
      git \
      build-essential \
      ca-certificates \
      curl \
      unzip \
      python3-dev \
      python3-pip \
      python3-setuptools \
      libffi-dev \
      libssl-dev \
      pkg-config \
      cython3 \
      && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  # Install Miniconda for Python 3.6 using wget with retry logic
  ENV CONDA_DIR=/opt/conda
  RUN wget --tries=5 --retry-connrefused https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-py36_4.9.2-Linux-x86_64.sh -O /tmp/miniconda.sh && \
      bash /tmp/miniconda.sh -b -p $CONDA_DIR && \
      rm /tmp/miniconda.sh && \
      $CONDA_DIR/bin/conda clean -tipsy
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/bin:$PATH
  # Create conda environment with python 3.6
  RUN conda create -n reltr python=3.6 -y
  SHELL ["conda", "run", "-n", "reltr", "/bin/bash", "-c"]
  # Activate conda environment and install packages
  RUN conda install pytorch==1.6.0 torchvision==0.7.0 cpuonly -c pytorch -y && \
      conda install matplotlib scipy numpy cython -y
  # Install pycocotools from github
  RUN pip install -U 'git+https://github.com/cocodataset/cocoapi.git#subdirectory=PythonAPI'
  # Clone the RelTR repository
  RUN git clone https://github.com/yrcong/RelTR.git /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  # Build native code for IoU computation and cython extension
  RUN cd lib/fpn && \
      sh make.sh && \
      python setup.py build_ext --inplace && \
      cd ../../
  # Set working directory and default shell
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  ENV CONDA_DEFAULT_ENV=reltr
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/envs/reltr/bin:$PATH
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 5 ---

  ENV CONDA_DIR=/opt/conda
  RUN set -ex; \
      curl -fSL https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-py36_4.9.2-Linux-x86_64.sh -o /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      bash /tmp/miniconda.sh -b -p $CONDA_DIR; \
      rm /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      $CONDA_DIR/bin/conda clean -tipsy
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/bin:$PATH
  RUN conda create -n reltr python=3.6 -y
  SHELL ["conda", "run", "-n", "reltr", "/bin/bash", "-c"]
  RUN conda install pytorch==1.6.0 torchvision==0.7.0 cpuonly -c pytorch -y && \
      conda install matplotlib scipy numpy cython -y
  RUN pip install -U 'git+https://github.com/cocodataset/cocoapi.git#subdirectory=PythonAPI'
  RUN git clone https://github.com/yrcong/RelTR.git /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  RUN cd lib/fpn && \
      sh make.sh && \
      python setup.py build_ext --inplace && \
      cd ../../
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  ENV CONDA_DEFAULT_ENV=reltr
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/envs/reltr/bin:$PATH
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 6 ---

      bash /tmp/miniconda.sh -b -p $CONDA_DIR; \
      rm /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      $CONDA_DIR/bin/conda clean -tipsy

  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      wget \
      git \
      build-essential \
      ca-certificates \
      curl \
      unzip \
      python3-dev \
      python3-pip \
      python3-setuptools \
      libffi-dev \
      libssl-dev \
      pkg-config \
      cython3 \
      bzip2 \
      && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  ENV CONDA_DIR=/opt/conda
  RUN set -ex; \
      wget --tries=5 --retry-connrefused https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-py36_4.9.2-Linux-x86_64.sh -O /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      bash /tmp/miniconda.sh -b -p $CONDA_DIR; \
      rm /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      $CONDA_DIR/bin/conda clean -tipsy
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/bin:$PATH
  RUN conda create -n reltr python=3.6 -y
  SHELL ["conda", "run", "-n", "reltr", "/bin/bash", "-c"]
  RUN conda install pytorch==1.6.0 torchvision==0.7.0 cpuonly -c pytorch -y && \
      conda install matplotlib scipy numpy cython -y
  RUN pip install -U 'git+https://github.com/cocodataset/cocoapi.git#subdirectory=PythonAPI'
  RUN git clone https://github.com/yrcong/RelTR.git /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  RUN cd lib/fpn && \
      sh make.sh && \
      python setup.py build_ext --inplace && \
      cd ../../
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  ENV CONDA_DEFAULT_ENV=reltr
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/envs/reltr/bin:$PATH
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 8 ---

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:20.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  ENV LANG=C.UTF-8 LC_ALL=C.UTF-8
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      wget \
      git \
      build-essential \
      ca-certificates \
      curl \
      unzip \
      python3-dev \
      python3-pip \
      python3-setuptools \
      libffi-dev \
      libssl-dev \
      pkg-config \
      cython3 \
      bzip2 \
      && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  ENV CONDA_DIR=/opt/conda
  RUN set -ex; \
      curl -fSL --retry 5 --retry-delay 5 https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh -o /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      bash /tmp/miniconda.sh -b -p $CONDA_DIR; \
      rm /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      $CONDA_DIR/bin/conda clean -tipsy
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/bin:$PATH
  RUN conda create -n reltr python=3.6 -y
  SHELL ["conda", "run", "-n", "reltr", "/bin/bash", "-c"]
  RUN conda install pytorch==1.6.0 torchvision==0.7.0 cpuonly -c pytorch -y && \
      conda install matplotlib scipy numpy cython -y
  RUN pip install -U 'git+https://github.com/cocodataset/cocoapi.git#subdirectory=PythonAPI'
  RUN git clone https://github.com/yrcong/RelTR.git /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  RUN cd lib/fpn && \
      sh make.sh && \
      python setup.py build_ext --inplace && \
      cd ../../
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  ENV CONDA_DEFAULT_ENV=reltr
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/envs/reltr/bin:$PATH
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]
--- End of Iteration 10 ---

  - **Modify PyTorch installation to CPU-only**:  
    - Run: `conda install pytorch==1.6.0 torchvision==0.7.0 cpuonly -c pytorch -y`

    - `conda install matplotlib scipy numpy cython -y`

  - `cd lib/fpn`  
  - Run: `sh make.sh` (build native code for IoU computation — CPU version)  
  - Build cython extension:  
    - Run: `python setup.py build_ext --inplace`  
    - Ensure no errors during compilation  
  - `cd ../../`

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:20.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  ENV LANG=C.UTF-8 LC_ALL=C.UTF-8
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      wget \
      git \
      build-essential \
      ca-certificates \
      curl \
      unzip \
      python3-dev \
      python3-pip \
      python3-setuptools \
      libffi-dev \
      libssl-dev \
      pkg-config \
      cython3 \
      bzip2 \
      && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  ENV CONDA_DIR=/opt/conda
  RUN set -ex; \
      wget --tries=5 --waitretry=5 -O /tmp/miniconda.sh https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-py36_4.12.0-Linux-x86_64.sh; \
      chmod +x /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      /tmp/miniconda.sh -b -p $CONDA_DIR; \
      rm /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      $CONDA_DIR/bin/conda clean -tipsy
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/bin:$PATH
  RUN conda create -n reltr python=3.6 -y
  SHELL ["conda", "run", "-n", "reltr", "/bin/bash", "-c"]
  RUN conda install pytorch==1.6.0 torchvision==0.7.0 cpuonly -c pytorch -y && \
      conda install matplotlib scipy numpy cython -y
  RUN pip install -U 'git+https://github.com/cocodataset/cocoapi.git#subdirectory=PythonAPI'
  RUN git clone https://github.com/yrcong/RelTR.git /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  RUN cd lib/fpn && \
      sh make.sh && \
      python setup.py build_ext --inplace && \
      cd ../../
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  ENV CONDA_DEFAULT_ENV=reltr
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/envs/reltr/bin:$PATH
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]

  **Step 1: Install Miniconda or Anaconda** (unchanged)  
  - Install Miniconda/Anaconda with Python 3.6 support  
  - Verify `conda` command availability  
  **Step 2: Clone RelTR repository**  
  - `git clone https://github.com/yrcong/RelTR.git`  
  - `cd RelTR`  
  **Step 3: Create and activate conda environment**  
  - Run: `conda create -n reltr python=3.6 -y`  
  - Run: `conda activate reltr`  
  **Step 4: Install PyTorch and dependencies**  
  - **Modify PyTorch installation to CPU-only**:  
    - Run: `conda install pytorch==1.6.0 torchvision==0.7.0 cpuonly -c pytorch -y`  
    - (Do NOT install cudatoolkit 10.1 or CUDA-dependent packages)  
  - Install other packages:  
    - `conda install matplotlib scipy numpy cython -y`  
  - Install pycocotools:  
    - `pip install -U 'git+https://github.com/cocodataset/cocoapi.git#subdirectory=PythonAPI'`

  **Step 6: Prepare Visual Genome dataset** (unchanged)  
  **Step 7: Prepare Open Images V6 dataset** (unchanged)

  - `cd lib/fpn`  
  - Run: `sh make.sh` (build native code for IoU computation — CPU version)  
  - Build cython extension:  
    - Run: `python setup.py build_ext --inplace`  
    - Ensure no errors during compilation  
  - `cd ../../`  
  **Step 9: Verify environment setup**  
  - Run Python imports:  
    ```python  
    import torch  
    import matplotlib  
    import scipy  
    import numpy  
    import cython  
    ```


  ---
  ### Additional Notes and Recommendations
  - **CPU-only PyTorch**: Using `cpuonly` package ensures no CUDA dependencies installed, avoiding runtime errors on GPU-less machines.  
  - **Performance**: Without GPU, expect slower training and inference times; adjust batch sizes and epochs accordingly.  
  - **Compilation**: Compilation scripts (`sh make.sh`, `python setup.py build_ext`) target CPU native code and cython extensions; ensure build tools (gcc, g++, python-dev headers) are installed on OS.  
  - **Operating system**: Use Ubuntu/Debian base images or native OS matching x86_64 linux architecture; verify all build tools and dependencies are installed (`build-essential`, `python3-dev`, etc.).  
  - **Paths**: Working directory is `/home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR` — ensure any hardcoded absolute paths in scripts or configs are updated accordingly if necessary.  
  - **Docker**: If containerizing, use an amd64 CPU base image (Ubuntu 20.04 or similar), install necessary build tools and dependencies, skip CUDA drivers/toolkit.  
  - **No GPU-specific instructions or configurations needed**; remove all CUDA environment variables and GPU driver install steps.  
  - **Ensure environment isolation**: Keep the conda environment dedicated to RelTR to avoid dependency conflicts.  
  ---
  This adjusted plan ensures compatibility and smooth operation on the given hardware environment, which is a CPU-only x86_64 Linux system without NVIDIA GPU or CUDA support.

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:20.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  ENV LANG=C.UTF-8 LC_ALL=C.UTF-8
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      wget \
      git \
      build-essential \
      ca-certificates \
      curl \
      unzip \
      python3-dev \
      python3-pip \
      python3-setuptools \
      libffi-dev \
      libssl-dev \
      pkg-config \
      cython3 \
      bzip2 \
      && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  ENV CONDA_DIR=/opt/conda
  RUN set -ex; \
      wget --tries=5 --waitretry=5 -O /tmp/miniconda.sh https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-py38_4.12.0-Linux-x86_64.sh; \
      chmod +x /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      /tmp/miniconda.sh -b -p $CONDA_DIR; \
      rm /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      $CONDA_DIR/bin/conda clean -tipsy
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/bin:$PATH
  RUN conda create -n reltr python=3.6 -y
  SHELL ["conda", "run", "-n", "reltr", "/bin/bash", "-c"]
  RUN conda install pytorch==1.6.0 torchvision==0.7.0 cpuonly -c pytorch -y && \
      conda install matplotlib scipy numpy cython -y && \
      conda install -c conda-forge gcc_linux-64 gxx_linux-64 libffi -y
  RUN pip install -U 'git+https://github.com/cocodataset/cocoapi.git#subdirectory=PythonAPI'
  RUN git clone https://github.com/yrcong/RelTR.git /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  RUN conda run -n reltr bash -c "cd lib/fpn && \
      sh make.sh && \
      python setup.py build_ext --inplace"
  ENV CONDA_DEFAULT_ENV=reltr
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/envs/reltr/bin:$PATH
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:20.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  ENV LANG=C.UTF-8 LC_ALL=C.UTF-8
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini
  RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      wget \
      git \
      build-essential \
      ca-certificates \
      curl \
      unzip \
      python3-dev \
      python3-pip \
      python3-setuptools \
      libffi-dev \
      libssl-dev \
      pkg-config \
      cython3 \
      bzip2 \
      && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  ENV CONDA_DIR=/opt/conda
  RUN set -ex; \
      wget --tries=5 --waitretry=5 -O /tmp/miniconda.sh https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-py38_4.12.0-Linux-x86_64.sh; \
      chmod +x /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      /tmp/miniconda.sh -b -p $CONDA_DIR; \
      rm /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      $CONDA_DIR/bin/conda clean -tipsy
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/bin:$PATH
  RUN conda create -n reltr python=3.6 -y
  SHELL ["conda", "run", "-n", "reltr", "/bin/bash", "-c"]
  RUN conda install pytorch==1.6.0 torchvision==0.7.0 cpuonly -c pytorch -y && \
      conda install matplotlib scipy numpy cython -y && \
      conda install -c conda-forge gcc_linux-64 gxx_linux-64 libffi -y
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini
  RUN git clone https://github.com/yrcong/RelTR.git RelTR
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  RUN pip install --upgrade pip && \
      pip install -U 'git+https://github.com/cocodataset/cocoapi.git#subdirectory=PythonAPI'
  RUN bash -c "cd lib/fpn && \
      sh make.sh && \
      python setup.py build_ext --inplace"
  ENV CONDA_DEFAULT_ENV=reltr
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/envs/reltr/bin:$PATH
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:20.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  ENV LANG=C.UTF-8 LC_ALL=C.UTF-8
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini
  RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      wget \
      git \
      build-essential \
      ca-certificates \
      curl \
      unzip \
      python3-dev \
      python3-pip \
      python3-setuptools \
      libffi-dev \
      libssl-dev \
      pkg-config \
      cython3 \
      bzip2 \
      && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  ENV CONDA_DIR=/opt/conda
  RUN set -ex; \
      wget --tries=5 --waitretry=5 -O /tmp/miniconda.sh https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-py38_4.12.0-Linux-x86_64.sh; \
      chmod +x /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      /tmp/miniconda.sh -b -p $CONDA_DIR; \
      rm /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      $CONDA_DIR/bin/conda clean -tipsy
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/bin:$PATH
  RUN conda create -n reltr python=3.6 -y
  SHELL ["conda", "run", "-n", "reltr", "/bin/bash", "-c"]
  RUN conda install pytorch==1.6.0 torchvision==0.7.0 cpuonly -c pytorch -y && \
      conda install matplotlib scipy numpy cython -y && \
      conda install -c conda-forge gcc_linux-64 gxx_linux-64 libffi -y && \
      pip install --upgrade pip
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini
  RUN git clone https://github.com/yrcong/RelTR.git RelTR
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  RUN pip install -U cython && \
      pip install -U 'git+https://github.com/cocodataset/cocoapi.git#subdirectory=PythonAPI'
  RUN bash -c "cd lib/fpn && \
      sh make.sh && \
      python setup.py build_ext --inplace"
  ENV CONDA_DEFAULT_ENV=reltr
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/envs/reltr/bin:$PATH
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]

  FROM ubuntu:20.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  ENV LANG=C.UTF-8 LC_ALL=C.UTF-8
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini
  RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      wget \
      git \
      build-essential \
      ca-certificates \
      curl \
      unzip \
      python3-dev \
      python3-pip \
      python3-setuptools \
      libffi-dev \
      libssl-dev \
      pkg-config \
      cython3 \
      bzip2 \
      gcc \
      g++ \
      make \
      libpython3-dev \
      libjpeg-dev \
      zlib1g-dev \
      && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  ENV CONDA_DIR=/opt/conda
  RUN set -ex; \
      wget --tries=5 --waitretry=5 -O /tmp/miniconda.sh https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-py38_4.12.0-Linux-x86_64.sh; \
      chmod +x /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      /tmp/miniconda.sh -b -p $CONDA_DIR; \
      rm /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      $CONDA_DIR/bin/conda clean -tipsy
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/bin:$PATH
  RUN conda create -n reltr python=3.6 -y
  SHELL ["conda", "run", "-n", "reltr", "/bin/bash", "-c"]
  RUN conda install pytorch==1.6.0 torchvision==0.7.0 cpuonly -c pytorch -y && \
      conda install matplotlib scipy numpy cython setuptools wheel -y && \
      conda install -c conda-forge gcc_linux-64 gxx_linux-64 libffi -y && \
      pip install --upgrade pip setuptools wheel
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini
  RUN git clone https://github.com/yrcong/RelTR.git RelTR
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  RUN pip install --upgrade cython && \
      pip install -U 'git+https://github.com/cocodataset/cocoapi.git#subdirectory=PythonAPI'
  RUN bash -c "cd lib/fpn && \
      sh make.sh && \
      python setup.py build_ext --inplace"
  ENV CONDA_DEFAULT_ENV=reltr
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/envs/reltr/bin:$PATH
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]

  ### Additional Notes and Recommendations
  - **CPU-only PyTorch**: Using `cpuonly` package ensures no CUDA dependencies installed, avoiding runtime errors on GPU-less machines.  
  - **Performance**: Without GPU, expect slower training and inference times; adjust batch sizes and epochs accordingly.  
  - **Compilation**: Compilation scripts (`sh make.sh`, `python setup.py build_ext`) target CPU native code and cython extensions; ensure build tools (gcc, g++, python-dev headers) are installed on OS.  
  - **Operating system**: Use Ubuntu/Debian base images or native OS matching x86_64 linux architecture; verify all build tools and dependencies are installed (`build-essential`, `python3-dev`, etc.).  
  - **Paths**: Working directory is `/home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR` — ensure any hardcoded absolute paths in scripts or configs are updated accordingly if necessary.  
  - **Docker**: If containerizing, use an amd64 CPU base image (Ubuntu 20.04 or similar), install necessary build tools and dependencies, skip CUDA drivers/toolkit.  
  - **No GPU-specific instructions or configurations needed**; remove all CUDA environment variables and GPU driver install steps.  
  - **Ensure environment isolation**: Keep the conda environment dedicated to RelTR to avoid dependency conflicts.  
  ---
  This adjusted plan ensures compatibility and smooth operation on the given hardware environment, which is a CPU-only x86_64 Linux system without NVIDIA GPU or CUDA support.

  FROM ubuntu:20.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  ENV LANG=C.UTF-8 LC_ALL=C.UTF-8
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini
  RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      wget \
      git \
      build-essential \
      ca-certificates \
      curl \
      unzip \
      python3-dev \
      python3-pip \
      python3-setuptools \
      libffi-dev \
      libssl-dev \
      pkg-config \
      cython3 \
      bzip2 \
      gcc \
      g++ \
      make \
      libpython3-dev \
      libjpeg-dev \
      zlib1g-dev \
      && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  ENV CONDA_DIR=/opt/conda
  RUN set -ex; \
      wget --tries=5 --waitretry=5 -O /tmp/miniconda.sh https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-py38_4.12.0-Linux-x86_64.sh; \
      chmod +x /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      /tmp/miniconda.sh -b -p $CONDA_DIR; \
      rm /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      $CONDA_DIR/bin/conda clean -tipsy
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/bin:$PATH
  RUN conda create -n reltr python=3.6 -y
  SHELL ["conda", "run", "-n", "reltr", "/bin/bash", "-c"]
  RUN conda install -y cython setuptools wheel && \
      conda install pytorch==1.6.0 torchvision==0.7.0 cpuonly -c pytorch -y && \
      conda install matplotlib scipy numpy -y && \
      conda install -c conda-forge gcc_linux-64 gxx_linux-64 libffi -y && \
      pip install --upgrade pip
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini
  RUN git clone https://github.com/yrcong/RelTR.git RelTR
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  RUN pip install -U 'git+https://github.com/cocodataset/cocoapi.git#subdirectory=PythonAPI'
  RUN bash -c "cd lib/fpn && \
      sh make.sh && \
      python setup.py build_ext --inplace"
  ENV CONDA_DEFAULT_ENV=reltr
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/envs/reltr/bin:$PATH
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]

DOCKERFILE:
  FROM ubuntu:20.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  ENV LANG=C.UTF-8 LC_ALL=C.UTF-8
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini
  RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      wget \
      git \
      build-essential \
      ca-certificates \
      curl \
      unzip \
      python3-dev \
      python3-pip \
      python3-setuptools \
      libffi-dev \
      libssl-dev \
      pkg-config \
      cython3 \
      bzip2 \
      gcc \
      g++ \
      make \
      libpython3-dev \
      libjpeg-dev \
      zlib1g-dev \
      && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  ENV CONDA_DIR=/opt/conda
  RUN set -ex; \
      wget --tries=5 --waitretry=5 -O /tmp/miniconda.sh https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-py38_4.12.0-Linux-x86_64.sh; \
      chmod +x /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      /tmp/miniconda.sh -b -p $CONDA_DIR; \
      rm /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      $CONDA_DIR/bin/conda clean -tipsy
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/bin:$PATH
  RUN conda create -n reltr python=3.6 -y
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  RUN source $CONDA_DIR/etc/profile.d/conda.sh && conda activate reltr && \
      conda install -y cython setuptools wheel && \
      conda install pytorch==1.6.0 torchvision==0.7.0 cpuonly -c pytorch -y && \
      conda install matplotlib scipy numpy -y && \
      conda install -c conda-forge gcc_linux-64 gxx_linux-64 libffi -y && \
      pip install --upgrade pip
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini
  RUN git clone https://github.com/yrcong/RelTR.git RelTR
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  RUN source $CONDA_DIR/etc/profile.d/conda.sh && conda activate reltr && \
      pip install --no-cache-dir -v -U 'git+https://github.com/cocodataset/cocoapi.git#subdirectory=PythonAPI'
  RUN source $CONDA_DIR/etc/profile.d/conda.sh && conda activate reltr && \
      cd lib/fpn && \
      sh make.sh && \
      python setup.py build_ext --inplace
  ENV CONDA_DEFAULT_ENV=reltr
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/envs/reltr/bin:$PATH
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  CMD ["/bin/bash"]

  FROM ubuntu:20.04
  ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
  ENV LANG=C.UTF-8 LC_ALL=C.UTF-8
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini
  RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
      wget \
      git \
      build-essential \
      ca-certificates \
      curl \
      unzip \
      python3-dev \
      python3-pip \
      python3-setuptools \
      libffi-dev \
      libssl-dev \
      pkg-config \
      cython3 \
      bzip2 \
      gcc \
      g++ \
      make \
      libpython3-dev \
      libjpeg-dev \
      zlib1g-dev \
      && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*
  ENV CONDA_DIR=/opt/conda
  RUN set -ex; \
      wget --tries=5 --waitretry=5 -O /tmp/miniconda.sh https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-py38_4.12.0-Linux-x86_64.sh; \
      chmod +x /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      /tmp/miniconda.sh -b -p $CONDA_DIR; \
      rm /tmp/miniconda.sh; \
      $CONDA_DIR/bin/conda clean -tipsy
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/bin:$PATH
  RUN conda create -n reltr python=3.6 -y
  SHELL ["/bin/bash", "-c"]
  RUN source $CONDA_DIR/etc/profile.d/conda.sh && conda activate reltr && \
      conda install -y cython setuptools wheel && \
      conda install pytorch==1.6.0 torchvision==0.7.0 cpuonly -c pytorch -y && \
      conda install matplotlib scipy numpy -y && \
      conda install -c conda-forge gcc_linux-64 gxx_linux-64 libffi -y && \
      pip install --upgrade pip
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini
  RUN git clone https://github.com/yrcong/RelTR.git RelTR
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  RUN conda run -n reltr pip install --no-cache-dir -v -U 'git+https://github.com/cocodataset/cocoapi.git#subdirectory=PythonAPI'
  RUN conda run -n reltr bash -c "cd lib/fpn && sh make.sh && python setup.py build_ext --inplace"
  ENV CONDA_DEFAULT_ENV=reltr
  ENV PATH=$CONDA_DIR/envs/reltr/bin:$PATH
  WORKDIR /home/cc/EnvGym/data-gpt-4.1mini/RelTR
  CMD ["bash"]
